<subSubSection id="C33265462E1E3E5BA5D0987FAFCF8C34" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9736CD2E1E3E5BA5D0987FAFCF8C34" blockId="5.[498,1542,535,802]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
DISTRIBUTION AND ECOLOGY. Former records from the Azores (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB94B3C2E1E3E5BA112987FA99B8D24" author="Thomson CW" box="[1328,1506,536,562]" journalOrPublisher="London: Macmillan and Co" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref11742" refString="Thomson CW. 1873. The depths of the sea. London: Macmillan and Co., 527." title="The depths of the sea" type="book" year="1873">
<emphasis id="B95CEADF2E1E3E5BA112987FA99B8D24" box="[1328,1506,536,562]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Thomson, 1873</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
), and the Canary Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB94B3C2E1E3E5BA7289827AFCE8D4C" author="Thomson CW" box="[778,951,576,602]" journalOrPublisher="Challenger" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1876" part="1873" refId="ref11762" refString="Thomson CW. 1877. The voyage of the &quot; Challenger &quot;: the Atlantic, a preliminary account of the general results of the exploring voyage of H. M. S - &quot; Challenger &quot; during the year 1873 and the early part of the year 1876. Vol. 1. London: Macmillan and Co., 424." title="The voyage of the &quot; Challenger &quot;: the Atlantic, a preliminary account of the general results of the exploring voyage of H. M. S" type="journal article" year="1877">
<emphasis id="B95CEADF2E1E3E5BA7289827AFCE8D4C" box="[778,951,576,602]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Thomson, 1877</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB94B3C2E1E3E5BA7E69827A8238D4C" author="Schulze FE" box="[964,1114,576,602]" journalOrPublisher="M. S. ' Challenger ', Zoology" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 514" part="21" refId="ref11260" refString="Schulze FE. 1887. Report on the Hexactinellida collected by H. M. S. ' Challenger' during the years 1873 - 1876. Report on the scienti fi c results of the voyage of H. M. S. ' Challenger ', Zoology 21: 1 - 514." title="Report on the Hexactinellida collected by H. M. S. ' Challenger' during the years 1873 - 1876. Report on the scienti fi c results of the voyage of H" type="journal article" year="1887">
<emphasis id="B95CEADF2E1E3E5BA7E69827A8238D4C" box="[964,1114,576,602]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Schulze, 1887</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
), 2,789–4,022 m deep (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB94B3C2E1E3E5BA1479827AEBB8D94" author="Tabachnick KR &amp; Menshenina LL" editor="Hooper JNA &amp; Van Soest RWM" journalOrPublisher="New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1267 - 1280" refId="ref11689" refString="Tabachnick KR, Menshenina LL. 2002. Family Pheronematidae Gray, 1870. In: Hooper JNA, Van Soest RWM, eds. Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, 1267 - 1280." title="Family Pheronematidae Gray" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2" year="2002">
<emphasis id="B95CEADF2E1E3E5BA1479827AEBB8D94" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Tabachnick &amp; Menshenina, 2002</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the 
<emphasis id="B95CEADF2E1E3E5BA77E980FAF128D94" bold="true" box="[860,875,616,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">fi</emphasis>
rst 
<emphasis id="B95CEADF2E1E3E5BA7B3980FAFD98D94" bold="true" box="[913,928,616,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">fi</emphasis>
nding of the species in the South Atlantic, where it is thus far only known from the São Paulo Ridge (SW Atlantic) (present paper), at 3,060 m depth. The single specimen collected was growing on basaltic rock with other sponges likely of the same species, albeit in very low densities. No epibiontic macro- or megafauna could be seen from the images obtained (
<figureCitation id="13132A482E1E3E5BA7459961AFDE8C34" box="[871,935,774,802]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[524,589,1088,1110]" captionTargetBox="[498,1541,234,1075]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[498,1534,234,1060]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2 Poliopogon amadou specimen (MNRJ 17629). (A–C) Specimen in situ, (B and C) holotype; (D) Detail of skeleton meshes (200 mm). Full-size DOI: 10.7717/peerj.9431/fig-2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4624214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4624214/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
