<subSubSection id="C33265462E1E3E5BA5D09921A8F58A01" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9736CD2E1E3E5BA5D09921AE218C77" blockId="5.[498,1542,838,1303]" box="[498,600,838,865]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading id="D0DF81A12E1E3E5BA5D09921AE218C77" bold="true" box="[498,600,838,865]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="0">Remarks</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9736CD2E1E3E5BA5D09909A9998B46" blockId="5.[498,1542,838,1303]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The single specimen collected by the Iata Piuna expedition matches the original description of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB94B3C2E1E3E5BA6BF99F2AF258CA6" author="Thomson CW" box="[669,860,917,944]" journalOrPublisher="Challenger" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1876" part="1873" refId="ref11762" refString="Thomson CW. 1877. The voyage of the &quot; Challenger &quot;: the Atlantic, a preliminary account of the general results of the exploring voyage of H. M. S - &quot; Challenger &quot; during the year 1873 and the early part of the year 1876. Vol. 1. London: Macmillan and Co., 424." title="The voyage of the &quot; Challenger &quot;: the Atlantic, a preliminary account of the general results of the exploring voyage of H. M. S" type="journal article" year="1877">
<emphasis id="B95CEADF2E1E3E5BA6BF99F2AF258CA6" box="[669,860,917,944]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Thomson (1877)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
and redescription by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB94B3C2E1E3E5BA04299F2A9978CA6" author="Tabachnick KR &amp; Menshenina LL" box="[1120,1518,917,944]" editor="Hooper JNA &amp; Van Soest RWM" journalOrPublisher="New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1267 - 1280" refId="ref11689" refString="Tabachnick KR, Menshenina LL. 2002. Family Pheronematidae Gray, 1870. In: Hooper JNA, Van Soest RWM, eds. Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, 1267 - 1280." title="Family Pheronematidae Gray" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2" year="2002">
<emphasis id="B95CEADF2E1E3E5BA04299F2A9978CA6" box="[1120,1518,917,944]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Tabachnick &amp; Menshenina (2002)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
. The latter authors mentioned that whereas macramphidiscs are clearly separable from the smaller amphidiscs, separation of second and third categories as mesamphidiscs and micramphidiscs is not always straightforward. It is not clear to us whether 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB94B3C2E1E3E5BA1409E6AAEAA8B59" author="Tabachnick KR &amp; Menshenina LL" editor="Hooper JNA &amp; Van Soest RWM" journalOrPublisher="New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1267 - 1280" refId="ref11689" refString="Tabachnick KR, Menshenina LL. 2002. Family Pheronematidae Gray, 1870. In: Hooper JNA, Van Soest RWM, eds. Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. New York: Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, 1267 - 1280." title="Family Pheronematidae Gray" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2" year="2002">
<emphasis id="B95CEADF2E1E3E5BA1409E6AAEAA8B59" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Tabachnick &amp; Menshenina (2002)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
were referring to every specimen as a rule, the holotype included.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9736CD2E1E3E5BA5D09E3AA8F58A01" blockId="5.[498,1542,838,1303]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
